<p><font class="sectionTitleText">By: Gwen Chasan, VP Client Services</font>


<p>In response to the increased desire of many companies to establish standardized business practices, Nevo Technologies has risen to the fore as a learned and effective technology partner.  Our expertise in helping clients build a framework for lifecycle software development facilitates their ability to achieve project success repeatedly while, at the same time, improving communication with their business partners.  Nevo’s innovative, yet disciplined methodology has enabled our clients to excel at the intersection of business processes and technology.  From the establishment of an original project vision to deployment and post-implementation support, Nevo works with clients to identify the key drivers of success.

<p>In the initial phases of our engagement, Nevo works with the client to establish three key components:

<ul><li>Current level of process formality - what processes are consistently used at present?
</li><li>Process tolerance - what changes are the client capable and willing to adopt?
</li><li>Goals for formality - what is the envisioned end result of our engagement?
</li></ul>

<p>Based on the answers to these questions, we evaluate our client’s existing process assets, including best practices and successful templates.  Leveraging our client’s prior investments in business process - as determined by their existing process assets -  Nevo identifies a target process model that achieves the greatest synergy between our client’s goals and abilities.  Once Nevo and client have established this foundation of assets and goals, we develop a custom process model based on industry best practices, focusing on the prerequisites and deliverables of key components.

<p>Projects vary widely in size and complexity.  Simple tasks do not require a heavy, formal process, whereas a lightweight, casual approach to critical, complex projects leads inevitably to increased project risk.  To achieve a flexibility of approach that leads to success in a wide array of projects, Nevo works with the client to create at least two views of lifecycle approach.  We begin by creating a lifecycle model geared towards the successful completion of large, multifaceted projects.  We then trim this process to create a lightweight approach suitable for smaller, more straightforward projects.  The result is the retention - in both iterations - of the core processes and deliverables, the steps and results that must be achieved regardless of the project size.

<p>Once Nevo has realized a strong process framework, we identify templates for each deliverable to ensure consistency and predictability.  The goal of this process is to reduce the burden on technologists and project managers by equipping them with a strong set of pre-established tools.  Nevo often uses the client’s existing internal documents as a starting point for the template generation.  We then supplement the client’s documents with templates from our own collection.

<p>Our final task in a process development engagement is the creation of samples for each of the templates.  This is most effectively done in the context of an actual project.  Though this task may extend over several months, key artifact samples are typically generated and shared during the pilot projects of the process implementation.

<p>Collaboration in the development of a process for lifecycle software development is important.  Nevertheless, we at Nevo believe firmly that a thoughtful, effective process implementation plan is critical for success.  Changes in any operating process can be disruptive.  Often times, even with a successful process development, process initiatives fail in the adoption phase.  As a result, the task of developing a new process framework must strongly rely on an active communication initiative to inform all people in the organization of changes to come.  Nevo, therefore, assists our clients in the creation and execution of an effective communication, rollout, and adoption plan.  This ensures that the process, or process components, are well-received and adopted smoothly.  Integral to this effort are:
<ul><li>A high-level management mandate.
</li><li>Clear, early, and consistent communication.
</li><li>The creation of process aids, such as quick reference cards.
</li><li>The availability of existing templates and samples.
</li><li>One or more pilot projects.
</li></ul>

<p>We cannot stress enough the importance of success in the pilot projects.  They must be run with careful supervision.  Vigilance at this point ensures that the process is sufficiently tested while concurrently creating a core team of process experts.  These experts will become colleagues who have used the new process and feel ownership and pride in its effectiveness.

<p>Nevo’s success with process initiatives stems from our deep understanding of effective and appropriate lifecycle processes, our collaborative approach, and our commitment to developing the most powerful process for the reality of our client’s organization.  We welcome the opportunity to help our clients improve their IT results quickly and painlessly, aiding in the creation of the right processes at the right time.

